WINE QUALITY ANALYSIS¶

Wine quality analysis is a crucial aspect of the wine industry, as it helps wine makers and producers understand the characteristics and potential of their wine. With the growing popularity of data analysis and machine learning, the use of Python has become increasingly popular in the field of wine quality analysis.

Python provides a wide range of tools and libraries that can be used to analyze wine data, including libraries for data visualization, statistical analysis, and machine learning. This makes it an ideal tool for analyzing wine quality, as it allows wine experts to analyze large amounts of data quickly and efficiently, and to make informed decisions based on the results.

Wine quality analysis using Python can be used to analyze various aspects of wine, including its chemical composition, sensory characteristics, and aging potential. This information can be used to make informed decisions about the production, storage, and marketing of wine.

Hemant Thapa

In [41]:
group_data_price = price_df.price_value
group_names_price = price_df.country_key
group_mean_price = np.mean(group_data_price)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))
ax.barh(group_names_price, group_data_price, color='black')
labels = ax.get_xticklabels()
plt.setp(labels, rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
# Add a vertical line, here we set the style in the function call
ax.axvline(group_mean_price, ls='--', color='red')
# Now we move our title up since it's getting a little cramped
ax.title.set(y=1)
ax.set(xlim=[0, 60], xlabel='price ($)', ylabel='Countries',
       title='Wine price')
plt.show()
